    <div class="row">
        <div class="span12">
            <h2>1. Install VLC</h2>
            <p>Go to <a href="http://www.videolan.org/">VideoLAN webiste</a>, download and install VLC 2.0.3 or higher.</p>
            <h2>2. Install FireBreathed VLC</h2>
            <p>Click <a href="/downloads/FBVLC_0.0.0.6.msi">here</a> and install FireBreathed VLC.</p>
            <p>Go to your Windows "Advanced system settings" and add in your "Environment Variables...".</br>
               In "System variables", locate the "Path" variable and add the path to the VLC folder.</br>
               (ex: ";C:\Program Files (x86)\VideoLAN\VLC")
            </p>
            <h2>3. Finish</h2>
            <p>Just restart your web browser</p>
